    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-09-12T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-09-12T13:00:00-05:00" n="551"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d551">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320.2<gloss target="#t_AA1">AA</gloss>/9–1250:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-09-12T20:00:00+02:00"
                            >September 12, 1950—8 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>270. Reference to <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 194 September 6,<note
                        n="1" xml:id="d551fn1">Not printed; but see footnote 1, <ref
                            target="#pg_986">p. 986</ref>.</note> I spoke to Acting Minister Foreign
                    Affairs this morning about Egypt’s contribution for Arab refugees. He told me
                    that the Government had authorized him to sign an agreement on the basis of the
                        <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> quota. I gave reasons for my opinion that
                    this was not enough. He said he would take it up again with the Council of
                    Ministers.</p>
                <p>I told him that in my opinion it is urgent for the Government to do something
                    about settling some of the Gaza refugees in Sinai peninsula. He promised to look
                    into that too.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 270, repeated unnumbered Arab capitals.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
